content: Yes, that was a memorable moment for sure! Seth Rollins' cash-in was one of the most dramatic and surprising cash-ins in Money in the Bank history. After the main event match between Brock Lesnar and Roman Reigns, Rollins' music hit and he ran down to the ring with his Money in the Bank briefcase. He cashed it in mid-match, turning the singles match into a triple threat match, and eventually won the WWE World Heavyweight Championship, making it his first world championship reign in WWE.
